The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Indian ref gets Athens call-up
Kochi: Fifa has selected Bentla DCoth, Fifa referee, to officiate the Olympic football tournaments in Athens from August 11 to 28. Bentla is the only referee from the Asian continent, who has been selected to officiate in the Olympics, KFA said in a press release on Monday. This is a great achievement for Indian football, especially for Kerala as this was the first time ever in the history of Indian football, an Indian woman is figuring in Olympics, the release said. Bentla is also the first Indian woman to become an international football referee in 2000. Since then, she has officiated many international matches, including Asian Games, pre-Olympic tournament in Fiji and Japan and south East Asean Games. She is presently officiating the Asian football womens under-19 tournament in china, which began on Monday. K.N. Shankar is the other Indian to have officiated in matches at top-level tournaments having been the assistant referee at two World Cups.  (PTI)  Copyright 
